15. We recommended that Management comply with the requirements of the provisions of Republic Act (RA) No. 9184. RA 9184 further provides that "in the preparation of the indicative APP, the end-user or implementing units of the Procuring Entity shall formulate their respective PPMP for their different PAPs. PPMP shall include:
a. Information on whether PAPs will be contracted out, implemented by administration or consigned;
b. The type and objective of contract to be employed;
c. The extent/size of contract scopes/packages.
d. The procurement methods to be adopted, and indicating if the procurement tasks are to be outsourced as provided in Sec of the IRR;
e. The time schedule for each procurement activity and for the contract implementation; and
f. The estimated budget for the general components
16. The PPMPs included in the budget proposal shall be forwarded to the BAC Secretariat for consolidation into an indicative APP and to the BAC for final recommendation of the appropriate procurement modality.
17. Changes to the individual PPMPs and the consolidated APP may be undertaken every 6 months or as often as may be required by the HOPE. The respective end-user or implementing units of the PE shall be responsible for the changes to the PPMPs, while the BAC Secretariat shall be responsible for the consolidation of these PPMPs into the APP, subject to approval by the HOPE.
18. We also recommended that Management prepare PPMP at the beginning of the year in support of the APP, in order to have a well-planned and coordinated procurement, thus achieving economy and efficiency in government transactions.
